      Add empty/null statement (`;`)
      
      Per the Dart specification, a single `;` is the empty (null) statement.
      It can appear anywhere a statement is expected, e.g. as the body of an
      `if (cond) ;` form, after a `return;` continuation, or as a stray `;`
      in a function body. The grammar previously had no rule for this, so
      real-world code using it failed to parse.
      
      Adds an `empty_statement` rule and includes it in `_statement`. Affects
      packages such as `crypto_wallet_util` (`if (!isUint(n, 53)) ;`) and
      `littlefish_feature_user_pins` (`return; ;`).
      
      Reference: Dart Language Specification — Statements (emptyStatement).
